Hey Chase!

Attached is your soil test analysis and season plan. You'll notice that the
report indicates a deficiency in the big 3 macros, but moreso with Nitrogen
and Potassium, which is why my product recommendations focus on those
primarily. Potassium will be the biggest help leading up to the summer
months. If these were my results, I'd get a full application of the Humate
down this spring and I'd favor the ProPeat fertilizers because they are
coated in peat moss, which will also help during the summer. Great Basin
Turf carries ProPeat, but like I said, you need to ask if they will sell to
you.

Another product I'm excited about that's new this year that will help for
summer, and can be applied monthly, is called Hydr8
<https://yardmastery.com/products/hydr8-liquicuretm-soil-surfactant-wetting=
-agent>.
It's a liquid product, so it will need to be applied with a sprayer mixed
with water.

Give this a look. Feel free to reach out with any questions, anytime. Happy
to help!

